And a great number of angels stand and speak with him face to face, of whom one with more majestic mien addresses him in these words: “ Arise‚ martyr renowned3 arise‚ and have no con- cern for thyself; arise and join our beneficent companies as our fellow. To the full now hast thou done thy part in enduring the menace of suffering, and with a noble death to end it thy passion is all finished. Most invincible of soldiers, bravest of the brave, now the savage, cruel torments themselves tremble before thee their conqueror. God the Christ, who watched thee, makes up for them with endless life, and with generous hand crowns thee as the partner of his cross. Lay aside this mortal vessel, a fabric of earthen structure which dissolves and falls to pieces, and come in freedom to the skies.’' So speaks the angel, and thereupon the splendour within breaks through the closed doors, the piercing brightness of the hidden light reveals itself through the chinks. Amazed and frightened at this the keeper of the dismal doorway, on whom was laid the night-long task of watching that house of death,
